65th Street, west of Broadway, north side, showing intersection Broadway and Amsterdam, in site is the High School of Commerce.
Board of Education, N.Y.C.
  1930

The face of the photograph reads:
Above photo: W 65th St, west of Broadway - High School of Commerce 589/C2

On photo:
High school of Commerce - Manhattan - 65th St west of Broadway, N. Y. City 5522

Broadway, west side, from, but not including, 65th to 66th Streets. The Lincoln Square Building and Loew's Lincoln Square Arcade is at the left.

January 30, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

54 to 34 West 65th Street, south side, eastward between Broadway and Central Park West, showing a 5-story house, No. 52 being demolished by the Works Progress Administration. The 9-story building visible is the Liberty Storage warehouse (Nos. 48-50).
March 2, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

A general view southeastward from about West 65th Street and Broadway, showing a night view of Rockefeller Center at the left. Vaguely, in the right background, appear the towering structures that form the Grand Central-42nd Street skyline. The photographers vantage point is estimated by the writer and is not accurate.

1940

Gift of Miss M. V. Leavitt
title: General view - [Midtown Manhattan] - Rockefeller Center at night.
